Package <Unnamed>

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    CGInterface
    This interface must be implemented for assembly code generation.
    MIPSCGConstants
    Constants used for MIPS code generation only.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ArrayType
    Type for arrays (currently, only integer arrays).
    Code3a
    A list of TAC statements (Inst3a).
    Code3aGenerator
    This class implements all the methods for 3a code generation (NOTE: this class must be coded by the student; the methods indicated here can be seen as a suggestion, but are not actually necessary).
    ConstSymbol
    Symbol for an integer constant.
    Data3a
    Class for implementing initialized constants.
    Errors
    Predefined messages for most semantic/typing errors.
    ExpAttribute
    Wrapper class for a triple (type, code, place) associated to an expression in the parser.
    FunctionSymbol
    Symbol for functions (declarations/calls).
    FunctionType
    The type of a function is composed of a return type plus a list of types for its arguments (empty if none).
    Inst3a
    A three address code (TAC) instruction is composed of an operation code and three operands a,b,c; the operands are objects from the Operand3a class.
    LabelSymbol
    Symbol for program labels (mainly for function calls).
    MIPSCGTriplet<T>
    For MIPS code generator.
    MIPSCodeGenerator
    This is the MIPS code generator.
    MIPSRegAlloc
    Manages register allocation during assembler code generation.
    MIPSRegDesc
    Register descriptor for assembler code generation.
    Operand3a
    Abstract class for implementing TAC operands (which are also the "symbols" stored in the SymbolTable).
    SymbDistrib
    A simple new symbol generator for temporaries and labels.
    SymbolTable
    In order to manage scopes, the VSL symbol table is implemented as a stack of tables, each of them being a 'map' data structure (from string identifiers to symbols (Operand3a)).
    SymbolTable.SingleScopeTable
    A SingleScopeTable is one of the possibly several tables representing the different scopes in a program: one for the function level, then one scope per nested block in a program.
    Type
    Implementation of a generic type object.
    TypeCheck
    Type checking operations (NOTE: this class must be implemented by the student; the methods indicated here can be seen as suggestions; note that some minor checks can still be performed directly in VSLTreeParser.g).
    Util
    Utility methods for generating error and warning messages, as well as debugging settings.
    VarSymbol
    Symbol for a var Ident or an Array ident.
    VslComp
    Entry point of the compiler, containing the main function.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Inst3a.TAC
    Enumeration of all three-address code operators; most of them have self-explaining names.
